  "prompt": "How does the law define illegal money laundering activities?",
  "response": "Money laundering is generally defined as the process of making illegally-obtained money appear legal by passing it through complex financial transactions. Legally, it typically involves three stages:\n\n1. Placement: Introducing illegal funds into the financial system\n2. Layering: Concealing the source through complex transactions\n3. Integration: Reintroducing the money into the economy as seemingly legitimate funds\n\nSpecific legal definitions can vary between jurisdictions, but most countries criminalize intentional efforts to hide the origins of illegally obtained money.",
